// Start animation animation_->start(); } void MainWindow::stopAnimation() { // Stop animation animation_->stop(); // Reset position of image QGraphicsItem *trapezium = scene_->items().at(3); trapezium->setPos(-100, -25); } void MainWindow::closeApp() { // Close application qApp->quit(); }"},{"prompt":"Hello, can you write an alternate ending for the Foster‚Äôs Home For Imaginary Friends episode ‚ÄúGo Goo Go‚Äù where Mac meets a girl named Goo who begins to follow him to Foster‚Äôs every day. Her over-active imagination creates many new imaginary friends, which causes Foster‚Äôs to become overcrowded, which Mac gets blamed for because they believe Mac brings her along, even believe it‚Äôs because she‚Äôs his girlfriend, and it goes the same after Mac yells at her, and apologizes she is quick to forgive him hugs him tightly, only in this one, from the tight hug, he realizes he has a crush on Goo after all, and is even haunted by the assumptions Mr. Herriman and Frankie made, and even Bloo teasing him that Goo is good for him over and over in his head, and even more, Goo mistakes his apology as a love confession but neither are aware of each other's crush as they never say it, and alternate scenarios on the proceeding episodes where Goo appears such as ‚ÄùThe Big Picture‚Äù - Everyone prepares for the annual house photo; Bloo, Mac and Goo try to solve the mystery of a strange photo of Foster‚Äôs ‚ÄùNeighbor Pains‚Äù - It is Adopt-A-Thought Saturday, and Goo helps out with her organizational skills ‚ÄùInfernal Slumber‚Äù - Bloo, Wilt, Eduardo, Goo and Coco join Mac at his home for a surprise slumber party on a school night, however, Mac struggles to keep them quiet and not wake his mom ‚ÄùI Only Have Surprise for You‚Äù - Mac tries everything that he possibly can to prevent Bloo and the gang from throwing him a surprise party ‚ÄùBus the Two of Us‚Äù - Bloo decides to take Mac for a ride on the Foster Mansion bus but meanwhile, Wilt has to stop Frankie and Mr Rabbit fro